title: For Sale:  AR15 Rifle in .223/5.56 - Modular Weapons System + extras
location: Traverse City, Northern Lower Peninsula, Michigan
postcontent:
Howdy

For Sale is a new, truly unique, and unfired AR15 rifle.

This is the Marck 15 Hydra rifle from MGI Military in Maine, USA.  It is a modular weapons platform that allows you to change calibers while using the same basic rifle.

The caliber change can be completed without tools, due to the quick change design of the parts.  See how here: http://www.mgi-military.com/index.php?id=2&sub_id=24

The rifle is MIL-standard with the exception of the quick change parts - so you can use ANY standard rifle barrels, mags, fire control groups,bolt carrier groups, sights, that you want.

Simple as changing just a bolt and barrel on this system the user will be able to fire 7 plus calibers including .22 rimfire, .223/5.56, 6.5 grendel, 6.8 spc, .450 thumper, .458 socom, and the .50 beowulf.  In addition, with some of the specialized "AR conversion magazines" that are available for milspec ARs, you could shoot 7.62x39 Russian with just a bolt and barrel.

Further, MGI offers the following magwells for caliber conversion:  
https://www.mgi-military.com/store/index.php?category=9

Now that you know a little about the Marck 15 Hydra, let me tell you about mine:

This rifle was purchased as a complete MGI AR lower($499) and MGI QCB-D upper ($599) in January of last year.

MGI did not have any barrels in stock at the time of purchase, so I purchased a barrel, BCG, gas block, sights, etc to finish the rifle.

SPECS:
Mossberg OEM .223/5.56 AR Barrel, fully melonited inside and out. ($150)
DS ARMS gas block ($30)
Wilson Combat Stainless Steel gas tube ($20)
Overmolded Rubber ERGO Grip ($30)
Magpul MOE adjustable stock ($45)
Milspec front sight, rail mounted ($30)
Magpul MBUS folding rear sight ($50)
GG&G quick-disconnect sling plate, rail-mounted ($30)
KNS Precision QD sling swivel ($25)

I have about $1500 invested in this rifle.  That makes it slightly more expensive than the Hydra purchased direct from MGI, but consider the following:

Better Quality Barrel (MGI barrel is not chrome-lined nor is it melonited)
This gun comes with sights (Hydra does not)
Ergo Grip (MGI is a standard crappy AR grip)
Magpul Stock (MGI comes with crappy plastic adjustable)
$50 worth of sling hardware
No shipping/handling/transfer fees

I live near Traverse City.  I will drive to you a reasonable distance.  I prefer to meet in the parking lot of a firearms store, or other public place for transfer.

CASH ONLY.

I would prefer to shoot a mag of ammo thru the rifle to function test before selling - but I will let you decide if you want it in unfired condition or not.

Contact me thru Armslist to get phone number for questions.

PS - it's not a COLT, but they don't list MGI as a Manufacturer......

PSS - the mag in the pictures is NOT included with the rifle.  If you do not have any of your own mags I do have a 10rd ACS mag I will include for 10 bucks.

title: For Sale:  Polish PPS-43C Pistol
postcontent:
For sale is my Polish PPS-43C Pistol chambered in 7.62x25 Tokarev. This is a semi-auto version of the PPS-43, which is a Polish submachine gun. It was made in Radom, Poland and imported into the US by IO Inc. These pistols are no longer being manufactured or imported, so they are becoming harder and harder to find.

My pistol is BRAND NEW AND UNFIRED. It has been sitting in my safe since I purchased it in September of 2013. It will come with 4 35-round magazines, and has an upgraded Blackjack polyurethane recoil buffer to replace the normal oil-soaked leather buffer that is known to disintegrate after only a few magazines.

This pistol can be registered as an SBR with a Form 1, and with some simple work and a spare PPS-43 parts kit which are widely available online, the stock can be swapped out with a working model to create a really unique SBR. As it stands now the button used to open the stock has been fixed shut to comply with NFA and ATF laws in order to make this a pistol. Or, it can be left as is for a really fun pistol that shoots a powerful round.

Looking to sell this brand new, unfired pistol along with 4 magazines, all in the original factory box, for $400.

I will ONLY sell to NH residents with a valid NH Driver's License and Conceal Carry permit, which must be shown at time of sale. CASH ONLY, NO TRADES. I am serious about selling this, so I am looking for serious buyers. I reply to emails very quickly.

title: For Sale:  PTR-91 Scout Carbine
postcontent:
For sale is my PTR-91 SC (Scout Carbine) rifle. This is a HK-91 clone made by PTR Industries on original HK tooling. These are known as the finest HK-91 clones ever produced. It is chambered in .308 Winchester, but will also reliably shoot 7.62x51 NATO. 

This rifle features a 16" match-grade fluted barrel which is chrome lined, birdcage flash hider, removable picatinny rails on the handguard, as well as a welded picatinny scope rail on the upper receiver, eliminating the need for a claw mount. It has a pristine black finish, and shoots with incredible accuracy due in part to the roller-delayed blowback operation.

This rifle is in like-new condition, has less than 200 rounds through it and has been meticulously cared for. The bolt gap is well within spec at 0.015", and has been constantly monitored. The finish, as stated before, is in pristine like-new condition. It has a black polymer fixed stock and a black polymer trigger group/housing. The handguard is black and machined from aluminum.

If potential buyers are also interested, I have an extremely unique and rare German military surplus .22LR conversion kit for this rifle, which features a barrel insert, .22LR bolt and carrier, along with 2 20-round .22LR magazines which are designed to have the same weight as a loaded 20-round .308 magazine. It also comes in an original German milsurp carrying case with all original documentation and cleaning supplies. I will sell this for $500 along with the rifle if you are interested. I can provide pictures and more info upon request.

I am looking to sell this rifle, along with 5 surplus 20-round magazines in excellent condition, as well as the original PTR-91 hard case and original manual for $1100 OBRO. As stated above, I will also sell the .22 conversion kit for $500 with the purchase of this rifle.

I may consider trades for an Aimpoint PRO + Cash, or an AK, AR, or other semi-auto rifle.

I will ONLY sell to NH residents with a valid NH Driver's License and Conceal Carry permit, which must be shown at time of sale. CASH ONLY. LOCAL SALE ONLY, I ABSOLUTELY WILL NOT SHIP. I am serious about selling this, so I am looking for serious buyers. I reply to emails very quickly.

title: For Sale:  PREBAN AR15 (COLT Sp1) w/ letter. MINT! >100 rounds, 100% legal, no need to register!  CT ONLY!!!
postcontent:
This 1977 Colt SP1 (Vietnam era AR-15) is MINT!  It was owned for decades by an old farmer who fired a couple magazines through it when he first bought it, then stored it, oiled.  It has less than 100 rounds through it, and you can tell by how clean it is.  No carbon anywhere.  This is legitimate 100% COLT (the real deal holyfield, not Oly, not Bushmaster, but the Cadillac of them all-  COLT.)  Triangular handguards, pencil thin barrel, slab side magazine well, no forward assist, giant pin.  
This is the gun Arnold uses in the original Predator movie.  (Billy uses one also.)

This rifle will last well past your lifetime, and here is the best part:

I have a letter from Colt, confirming the production date according to the serial number, and it is indeed a preban.  Thus, this rifle is LEGAL to buy/sell/transfer within Connecticut.....for now.
January 2014, the AR15 landscape has changed.  Of course, since April 4, 2013, NO postban AR-15s could have been legally purchased or transferred within CT.  And, as of December 31, 2013, all postbans bought before 4/4/13 were required to be registered as Assault Weapons with the state of CT.

So, what is your option if you want an AR-15?  Well, you have two options:
Never buy one legally in Connecticut again, or 
Buy a preban AR, with NO NEED to register it, plus you can put as many modifications on it as you like, ALL 100% LEGAL!  What types of modifications? These:
*Collapsable or folding stock
*Pistol grip
*Flash suppressor
*Bayonet lug (and bayonet)
and more.

There is serious rumor and definite talk that this so-called loophole will be closed in the next legislative session (late January, this month!) so that law abiding CT citizens may no longer even purchase preban AR15s!

Good luck finding an FFL or gun shop to accept an out of state transfer of a preban.  Even the stores which were doing so, are no longer doing so in 2014.....

I live in the Bridgeport-New Haven area, and I am willing to travel.

This rifle will be sold according to all applicable rules and laws.  I will NOT sell this rifle out of state....it MUST stay in Connecticut!  So, Nutmeggers only need apply.

Email me, or text me at 2o3 -8one4 - 4four2five

I have more photos, if you like, just email me.  (Limited to three here on Armslist.)

This rifle will accept both 223 Remington and 5.56 NATO rounds.


I recently put 5 rounds through her during a trip to the range.  It was freezing cold out, with a driving, almost sideways rain.  Shooting from under the cover of the outdoor range roof, in the dark (there were some lights on pointed downrange, but it was still very dark out at 5:15pm in the rain!), I put all five shots on an 18 inch target at 70 yards, using iron sights, while standing!

title: For Sale:  Remington Model 700 BDL 6mm Remington Heavy Barrel
postcontent:
SALE IS PENDING

I have for sale an older Remington Model 700 BDL in 6mm Remington, Serial No 6646xxx.  It has a 24-inch Heavy Varmint or “bull” barrel.  I purchased this rifle used in 1999 because I “thought” I needed another varmint rifle, and these factory heavy-barreled rifles are somewhat hard to come by.  I no longer do much varmint hunting, and I still have a couple of good .22 cal rifles, so I am liquidating the excess.

This rifle is all original, except that the action has been pillar-bedded, the barrel free floated, and it wears a Pachmayr recoil pad.  The stock shows normal signs of use, i.e. the usual dings, dents, scuffs, scratches, etc. The bluing is in overall very nice condition.  The action is smooth, the safety works fine, and the trigger has been adjusted to a smooth, light pull, with virtually no creep.  The bore is smooth and shiny. 

The rifle comes with Burris 2-piece scope mounts and Burris Signature Series rings installed.  The scope shown in the photos is NOT included.

Sadly, the front end of the trigger guard is broken where the trap door latch is located (see bottom photo).  The latch is still functional, but the trigger guard assembly should probably be repaired.  I usually just loaded one round at a time and had no problem with it.

This rifle will routinely shoot 5-shot groups under 1-inch at 100 yards using Nosler 70 gr Ballistic Tip handloads.  I have probably fired only 200 rounds through it since I bought it.  It is a good shooter for sure!  I just don’t have use for it anymore.

The asking price is $750.  I will consider any reasonable offer. (Again....the scope is NOT included)

This is a CASH deal, no personal checks or Money Orders.  I will also accept PayPal plus 3 percent of the selling price to cover the transaction fees.  I prefer to sell to a fellow Arizona resident, because no FFL transfer in required, but will sell to an out-of-state buyer if he pays for all shipping and FFL transfer fees.  

.
